### ============================================================
### AUTHENTICATION API TESTS
### ============================================================
### 
### This file contains HTTP requests for testing the authentication module.
### It covers:
###   - Public endpoints (no token required)
###   - Protected endpoints (valid token required)
###   - Role-based access control (user, editor, admin)
###   - Authentication (login, logout, refresh)
###   - Error scenarios (invalid token, missing token, wrong role)
###
### Requirements:
###   - Extension: REST Client (humao.rest-client) for VS Code
###   - Server must be running on {{baseUrl}}
###   - Update {{accessToken}} after login
###
### ============================================================

### ============================================================
### VARIABLES (Update {{accessToken}} after successful login)
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@accessToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpZCI6MSwiZW1haWwiOiJqdWFuLnBlcmV6QGV4YW1wbGUuY29tIiwicm9sZSI6InVzZXIiLCJpYXQiOjE3Nzk3NjY5NzIsImV4cCI6MTc3OTc2Nzg3Mn0.y-yOvueaLSB3IdFpvovdROlSPOVitVLA9Uzqzcn6zMU

### ============================================================
### 1. AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS (Public)
### ============================================================

### 1.1 Login - Regular user (role: user)
# @name loginUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juan.perez@example.com",
  "password": "1234"
}

### 1.2 Login - Admin user (role: admin)
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "1234"
}

### 1.3 Login - Invalid credentials (should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### 1.4 Logout - Clear refresh token cookie
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/logout

### 1.5 Refresh - Get new access token using refresh token cookie
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/refresh

### ============================================================
### 2. TEST ENDPOINTS (Development only)
### ============================================================

### 2.1 Public endpoint - No token required
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/public

### 2.2 Public endpoint - With token (still works, public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/public
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 2.3 Protected endpoint - Valid token required
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 2.4 Protected endpoint - Missing token (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/protected

### 2.5 Get current user info - Token details
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### ============================================================
### 3. ROLE-BASED ACCESS CONTROL TESTS
### ============================================================

### 3.1 User-only endpoint - Should work (role: user)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/user
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3.2 Editor-only endpoint - Should fail (403) for regular user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/editor
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3.3 Admin-only endpoint - Should fail (403) for regular user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/admin
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3.4 Multi-role endpoint (admin, editor) - Should fail (403) for regular user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/multi-role
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### ============================================================
### 4. TOKEN DEBUGGING ENDPOINTS
### ============================================================

### 4.1 Decode token without verification (only shows payload, no signature check)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/decode-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{accessToken}}"
}

### 4.2 Verify token with signature check (requires valid JWT_SECRET)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/verify-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{accessToken}}"
}

### ============================================================
### 5. ERROR SCENARIO TESTS
### ============================================================

### 5.1 Invalid token format (should return 403)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/protected
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.format.123

### 5.2 Expired token simulation (use a known expired token)
# GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/protected
# Authorization: Bearer <expired_token_here>

### 5.3 Nonexistent route (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/nonexistent-route

### 5.4 Missing Authorization header (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/protected

### ============================================================
### 6. QUICK TEST WORKFLOW (Recommended order)
### ============================================================
###
### 1. Run "Login - Regular user" to get an access token
### 2. Copy the accessToken from response and update @accessToken variable
### 3. Run "Protected endpoint - Valid token required" to verify token works
### 4. Run "User-only endpoint" to test role access
### 5. Run "Admin-only endpoint" to verify role restriction (should fail)
### 6. Run "Logout" to clear the refresh token cookie
###
### ============================================================

### ============================================================
### 7. EXPECTED RESPONSES REFERENCE
### ============================================================
###
### ┌─────────────────────┬──────────┬─────────────────────────────────┐
### │ Endpoint            │ Status   │ Description                     │
### ├─────────────────────┼──────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
### │ POST /login         │ 200      │ Returns accessToken + user info │
### │ POST /login         │ 400      │ Missing email or password       │
### │ POST /login         │ 401      │ Invalid credentials             │
### │ POST /logout        │ 200      │ Clears cookie, returns success  │
### │ POST /refresh       │ 200      │ Returns new accessToken         │
### │ POST /refresh       │ 401      │ No refresh token cookie         │
### │ POST /refresh       │ 403      │ Invalid or expired refresh token│
### │ GET /test/public    │ 200      │ Always accessible               │
### │ GET /test/protected │ 200      │ Valid token required            │
### │ GET /test/protected │ 401      │ No token provided               │
### │ GET /test/protected │ 403      │ Invalid/expired token           │
### │ GET /test/user      │ 200      │ Role: user only                 │
### │ GET /test/editor    │ 403      │ Role: editor required           │
### │ GET /test/admin     │ 403      │ Role: admin required            │
### │ GET /test/multi-role│ 403      │ Role: admin or editor required  │
### └─────────────────────┴──────────┴─────────────────────────────────┘
###
### ============================================================